---
/**
 * WhatItIs — prose explanation + inline SVG architecture diagram.
 * Spec reference: section 11, section 23.
 *
 * Diagram dimensions: max 420px wide. Readable at 1x on mobile.
 * All text in the SVG uses the body font for consistency.
 */
---

<section
  class="section"
  id="what-it-is"
  aria-labelledby="what-it-is-heading"
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col">
      <!-- Prose -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="section-heading" id="what-it-is-heading">What it is</h2>

        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            An EDBMS manages the full lifecycle of typed, stateful business
            objects — entities. Where a standard database stores rows,
            CyodaLight tracks state transitions, enforces lifecycle rules,
            and maintains a temporal audit trail.
          </p>

          <p>
            You define your entity types: the fields they carry, the states
            they can be in, and the transitions between states. CyodaLight
            enforces those rules at the API boundary. Invalid transitions are
            rejected. Every valid transition is recorded immutably.
          </p>

          <p>
            Two storage modes are available. In-memory mode starts in under
            two seconds with zero external dependencies — useful for
            development and fast test cycles. PostgreSQL mode persists entity
            state durably across restarts for integration testing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Architecture SVG diagram -->
      <!--
        Spec section 11: "Static inline SVG. Dark text on light background."
        Spec defines the exact structure and labels.
      -->
      <div class="what-it-is__diagram">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 380 340"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          role="img"
          aria-labelledby="arch-diagram-title"
          width="380"
          height="340"
          style="max-width:100%;height:auto;font-family:var(--font-mono)"
        >
          <title id="arch-diagram-title">
            CyodaLight architecture: your application connects via gRPC to
            CyodaLight, which contains the Entity Store, Lifecycle Engine,
            and Audit Log. CyodaLight connects to either in-memory storage
            or PostgreSQL.
          </title>

          <!-- Background -->
          <rect width="380" height="340" rx="12" fill="#f1f5f9"/>
          <rect x="1" y="1" width="378" height="338" rx="11" fill="none" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1"/>

          <!-- "Your Application Code" box -->
          <rect x="100" y="20" width="180" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="190" y="45" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#0f172a" font-weight="600">Your Application Code</text>

          <!-- Arrow down -->
          <line x1="190" y1="60" x2="190" y2="80" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>
          <text x="205" y="75" font-size="11" fill="#475569">gRPC</text>

          <!-- CyodaLight binary box -->
          <rect x="60" y="80" width="260" height="130" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="190" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#475569" font-weight="500">CyodaLight</text>

          <!-- Inner rows -->
          <rect x="80" y="112" width="220" height="28" rx="4" fill="#eff6ff" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="190" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#1e40af" font-weight="500">Entity Store</text>

          <rect x="80" y="148" width="220" height="28" rx="4" fill="#eff6ff" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="190" y="167" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#1e40af" font-weight="500">Lifecycle Engine</text>

          <rect x="80" y="184" width="220" height="20" rx="4" fill="#eff6ff" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text x="190" y="198" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#1e40af">Audit Log</text>

          <!-- Arrow down -->
          <line x1="190" y1="210" x2="190" y2="235" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowhead)"/>

          <!-- Storage box: In-Memory OR PostgreSQL -->
          <rect x="60" y="235" width="260" height="76" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1.5"/>

          <!-- Divider line -->
          <line x1="190" y1="241" x2="190" y2="305" stroke="#e2e8f0" stroke-width="1"/>

          <!-- In-Memory label -->
          <text x="125" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#059669" font-weight="600">In-Memory</text>
          <text x="125" y="280" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#475569">0 dependencies</text>
          <text x="125" y="295" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#475569">resets on restart</text>

          <!-- OR label -->
          <text x="190" y="277" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#94a3b8" font-style="italic">OR</text>

          <!-- PostgreSQL label -->
          <text x="255" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#d97706" font-weight="600">PostgreSQL</text>
          <text x="255" y="280" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#475569">durable state</text>
          <text x="255" y="295" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#475569">persists on restart</text>

          <!-- Arrowhead marker -->
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="6" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
              <polygon points="0 0, 8 3, 0 6" fill="#94a3b8"/>
            </marker>
          </defs>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
